{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904011512,"sessionID":"ses_1d10fb151ffec2BZrFWYyNH7va","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"changes committed in PR #<NN>\n\nThis PR fixes the logical definition of **squamous epithelium** (UBERON:0006914) as requested in this issue. The `has_part` relation in the equivalence axiom was replaced with `composed_primarily_of`, ensuring that only epithelia primarily composed of squamous epithelial cells are classified as squamous epithelium. This aligns the logical definition with the existing text definition and standard anatomical usage.\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904011501,"end":1778904011510}},"id":"prt_e2ef10e4e001371w1ccL4awRUa","sessionID":"ses_1d10fb151ffec2BZrFWYyNH7va","messageID":"msg_e2ef1076f001nudxyPDK8jPVxE"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904017012,"sessionID":"ses_1d10fb151ffec2BZrFWYyNH7va","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"## Summary\n\nThis PR modifies the logical definition of **squamous epithelium** (UBERON:0006914) to address issue #3473.\n\n### Problem\n\nThe existing logical definition used `has_part some squamous epithelial cell`. This was overly broad: any epithelium containing even a single squamous epithelial cell (or a minority population) would be inferred as a subclass of squamous epithelium, which contradicts standard anatomical usage.\n\n### Change\n\nIn `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`, the equivalence axiom for UBERON:0006914 was updated:\n\n```diff\n- intersection_of: has_part CL:0000076 ! squamous epithelial cell\n+ intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000076 ! squamous epithelial cell\n```\n\nA `term_tracker_item` property value was also added to link the term to issue #3473.\n\n### Rationale\n\n- **Alignment with text definition**: The text definition states that a squamous epithelium is \"characterised by its most superficial layer consisting of squamous epithelial cells\". The term implies a primary composition, not merely the presence of such cells.\n- **Consistency with related issues**: A similar concern was raised in the Cell Ontology repository (obophenotype/cell-ontology#2671). Using `composed_primarily_of` is the standard pattern in Uberon for expressing that an entity is mainly made up of a particular cell type or tissue.\n- **Existing pattern**: Uberon already uses `composed_primarily_of` in logical definitions for other tissues (e.g., lymphoid tissue, ommatidium), confirming this is the appropriate relation.\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] Read the issue carefully and identified the requested change.\n- [x] Checked out the term using `obo-checkout.pl`.\n- [x] Verified the current term and its logical definition.\n- [x] Edited the checked-out term to use `composed_primarily_of` instead of `has_part`.\n- [x] Added a `term_tracker_item` property linking back to issue #3473.\n- [x] Checked the term back in using `obo-checkin.pl`.\n- [x] Verified the change was correctly applied to `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n- [x] Committed the change with a detailed, signed commit message.\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904017006,"end":1778904017010}},"id":"prt_e2ef1131a0011ulbao9wzzD6Hc","sessionID":"ses_1d10fb151ffec2BZrFWYyNH7va","messageID":"msg_e2ef1076f001nudxyPDK8jPVxE"}}
